[Attached is a patch that attempts to fix this.

Currently when any new block is created, first an RBW version is made and then it is finalized, passed to addFinalizedBlock() in BlockPoolSlice with the intended total block size.

By looking at the difference between getOriginalBytesReserved() and originalBytesReserved() it is possible to see how many bytes were actually written, and the dfsUsage can be increased by this amount. The usage for the meta file can be added directly since the old meta is removed upon new block creation.
